<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-25T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="773" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48/1407: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-25T19:00:00-05:00">January 25, 1938—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>39. Your 48, January 23, 5 p.m. For your information. The Department has
                            amended the text of the first sentence of your statement, contained in
                            the telegram under reference, to read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The hostilities are driving huge numbers of Chinese from their
                                    homes, in cities and villages and on farms. Fleeing from danger,
                                        <pb facs="0578" n="574" xml:id="pg_574"/> very many of these
                                    people become refugees and are in need of shelter, food,
                                    clothing, and medical aid.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>